headline: MetLife Names Adrienne O’Neill as Chief Accounting Officer
summary: NEW YORK, July 30, 2025--MetLife, Inc. (NYSE: MET) today announced that Adrienne O’Neill will join the company as Executive Vice President and Chief Accounting Officer, effective Sept. 2, 2025. She will report to John McCallion, Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer, and head of MetLife Investment Management.

headline: MetLife (MET): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, MetLife’s stock price fell to $77.68. Shareholders have lost 10.7% of their capital, which is disappointing considering the S&P 500 has climbed by 5%. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and might have investors contemplating their next move.
